COMMENTS: Actia . . . rostra: "Actian ship-beaks"Evoking the battle of Actium and, I add, the location itself (for instance the focus on the ship-beaks, which, I argue, are metonymy for the battle which took place on the sea). See Camps (1967), 70 for a discussion on the identification of these rostra and his suggestion that these are indicative of a Triumph.
